An interval describes the area between two numbers. It is understood to contain the near one and exlude the far.
A position with a direction. Describes a line in 3D
A special curve, describing a straight line. This is a curve with zero curvature and torsion.
A position with two directions. Describes a plane in 3D.
A special curve, describing a circle arc part. This is a curve with constant curvature and no torsion.
A position with two directions. Describes a plane in 3D.
A special curve, describing a helix. This is a curve with constant curvature and torsion.
A Clothoid or Euler-Cornu spiral with the property k = s/a²

A cubic curve of the form p(t(s)) = a + b*t + c*t² + d*t³. The parameter ist transformed by t(s) to arc length s.
The Rotator is a curve that constantly rotates (with respect to its arc length) in the plane and perpendicular to it.
Describes one rotator with two total angles and the total length.

Describe a spatial transformation, in general a translation by the Position element, followed by a rotation given by the three Vectors, wich would be the Tangent, Normal and Binormal directions of a TNB frame (or x, y,z axes respectively) in that order.
A special curve, describing the idiosyncratic curve type used in EEP.
Holds a curve that describes the spatial geometry of a track.
Placeholder to indicate no twist compared to the natural torsion of the curve.
A constant twist along the whole track.
Linear interpolated twist values between the ends of the track.
Describes value at a point along a track.
Describes the twist by defining several points along the track with distinct twist values that get liearly interpolated inbetween.
A twist that maintains a minimum angle of the binary vector towards a given direction.
Peep. Describes the top direction of a curve. A curve has a natural binormal direction, the twist describes a rotation of that direction around the tangent direction. Measured in radiants.
